-- Indian shares continue to retreat from record high on profit taking
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 06:05AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 28 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell on Monday for a second consecutive session, retreating from record highs hit in the previous session, as blue chips such as Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS> fell on profit-taking while choppy global shares also weighed.

L&T provisionally fell 1.6 percent ahead of its results later in the day, while Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd <HDFC.NS> ended lower 0.9 percent.